TEXT 9152 1344 Left 2 ;-you may temporarily have all of the switches in the Y position so that \nyou can determine the R1c_op and R2c_op parameter values that you \nneed for the compensation resistors\n \n-to put the switches in the Y position, simply delete the small horizontal\npiece of interconnect beneath the X label and place a small horizontal\npiece of interconnect beneath the Y label -- it is even easier if, for each\nswitch, you just move the small horizontal piece of interconnect over to\nthe position you want without deleting\n \n-once you get the resistor sizes you need, you MUST then place the \nswitches in the X position and use M1c, M2c devices as triode resistors,\nsetting the Lnc_op, Wnc_op, Mnc_op, Lpc_op, Wpc_op, and Mpc_op \nparameters to appropriate values\n \n-to put the switches in the X position, simply delete the small horizontal\npiece of interconnect beneath the Y label and place a small horizontal\npiece of interconnect beneath the X label -- it is even easier if, for each\nswitch, you just move the small horizontal piece of interconnect over to\nthe position you want without deleting\n \n-note that the triode mode resistance of the M1c and M2c devices will \nsimply be rds=1/gds, where gds is the triode conductance of either device\n \n-once you are ready to use M1c and M2c in place of the resistors R1c and \nR2c, put the switches into the X position, use one of the testbenches (e.g., \ntestbench_01) to fine-tune your M1c and M2c device sizes (all while keeping \nthe width, length, and device multiplier within the project constraints), and \nthen characterize your final design performance with all of the testbenches\n \n-your design is not considered to be finalized until all performance specs \nare met with the switches in the X position (but see below for additional\ndetails)\n \n-if and only if you decide that you do not need a compensation resistor for \nthe NMOS output device, then you should set all four SW1 switches in \nposition Y; if you do this, then set the R1c_op parameter to some small \nvalue (e.g., 1m, 1u, or 1n); if you additionally decide that you do not need a \ncompensation capacitor for the NMOS output device, then you should set \nthe C1c_op parameter to some small value (e.g., 1f)\n \n-if and only if you decide that you do not need a compensation resistor for \nthe PMOS output device, then you should set all four SW2 switches in \nposition Y; if you do this, then set the R2c_op parameter to some small \nvalue (e.g., 1m, 1u, or 1n); if you additionally decide that you do not need a \ncompensation capacitor for the PMOS output device, then you should set \nthe C2c_op parameter to some small value (e.g., 1f)
TEXT 7232 2512 Left 2 ;YOUR FINAL DESIGN MUST HAVE ALL SWITCHES IN POSITION X\n(but see the guidelines to the right for additional details)
